"t_title36","〈台北都會〉市長禮讓柯？民進黨︰議員席次恐掉6席
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  〔記者蕭婷方、楊淳卉／台北報導〕年底台北市長選舉，民進黨是否提名或要禮讓柯文哲，至今尚未明朗，民進黨基層近期不斷要求自提候選人，現更傳有深綠選民為不讓柯連任，已有「棄保」的投票傾向。 不過，據台灣民意基金會昨公布北市選情最新民意調查，民進黨自推候選人均不敵柯文哲。民進黨籍市議員許淑華則憂心市長提名與否牽動議員選情，許淑華說，民進黨若禮讓柯文哲，恐有十％左右重要選民不願出門投票，影響議員席次；四年前國民黨約有一成選民未投票，現在換成民進黨了，加上執政黨有執政包袱，議員席次本來就會掉，「選情雖不致崩盤，但（掉）五、六席一定會有」。 民進黨籍北市議員顏聖冠昨接受廣播媒體訪問時表示，近期已聽聞深綠支持者對柯極度厭惡，嗆「若民進黨不提名市長候選人，就寧可讓國民黨上」，甚至有許多死忠支持者言明，「舉凡與柯文哲走太近的議員，就要給他顏色看。」 不過，台灣民意基金會昨天公布台北市選情最新民意調查，民調結果雖發現三十七．三％選民認為民進黨應自推候選人，多於禮讓派五．四％，但是綠營現表態要角逐黨內提名參選北市長的立委姚文智、前副總統呂秀蓮、前台南縣長蘇煥智民調均不敵柯文哲。 民調結果更顯示，若民進黨立委姚文智出戰，在民進黨認同者中，有五十一％支持柯文哲，僅三十七％支持姚文智，六．三％支持丁守中，五·八％為不知道。 本次調查時間為二月二十四至二十五日，以台北市廿歲以上成年人進行電話抽樣調查，有效樣本一○七○人，抽樣誤差在九十五％信心水準下約正負三個百分點。 另外，外傳民進黨高層私下找有意參選台北市長的民進黨立委姚文智談話，提出只要姚的民調支持度低於廿％，就會禮讓現任台北市長柯文哲，關鍵時間點為今年五月。 姚文智昨天出席義光教會追思禮拜後被問到此事，回應「完全沒有聽過這樣說法」。 新聞送上來！快加入自由電子報APP、LINE好友  2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅 注目新聞 1 中國卡車罷工延燒 司機高喊「打倒共產黨」！ 2 新版身分證票選出爐 設計師魯少綸奪首獎！ 3 洋腸又來！夜店外帶18歲妹 網站取名「台女很容易」... 4 侯友宜妻1塊土地99個門牌 蘇貞昌：太荒唐 5 連俞涵超正弟媳曝光…根本巨乳林志玲！","7"
"t_title37","《TAIPEI TIMES》 Taipei mayor still favorite as residents change camp
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  POLITICAL VIEW: Taipei residents are conservative, a poll said, adding people support Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je’s decision not to remove statues of Chiang Kai-shek By Lee I-chia / Staff reporter An opinion poll published yesterday shows Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je （柯文哲） holds a comfortable lead in the year-end mayoral election, and indicated that Taipei residents’ political affiliation is shifting toward a pan-green majority. The Taiwanese Public Opinion Foundation yesterday released the results of its poll on how Taipei residents view Ko, based on the premise that Ko won the 2014 election on the strength of the Democratic Progressive Party’s （DPP） support base. However, as the Ko’s relationship with the DPP appears to have deteriorated, results of the Nov. 24 election are unpredictable, the foundation said. The foundation asked poll respondents if they would prefer the DPP nominating a candidate; a DPP member leaving the party to campaign; or a combination of the two scenarios, if Ko were running against a Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） candidate. According to the poll, 37.3 percent of respondents think the DPP should nominate its own candidate, 31.9 percent think the party should support Ko and 19.2 percent are neutral. Foundation chairman You Ying-lung （游盈隆） said the majority of voters who are more than 50 years old favor the DPP nominating its own candidate, while most of those under 50 felt the party should again support Ko. Former KMT legislator Ting Shou-chung （丁守中） has the most support （60.6 percent） among his party’s candidate hopefuls, while DPP Legislator Pasuya Yao （姚文智） leads （38 percent） among DPP hopefuls, the poll showed. Ko holds a solid support lead of 47.6 percent, beating Ting’s 25.2 percent and Yao’s 15.6 percent, the poll showed. According to the poll, 9.1 percent of voters view Ko’s administrative performance as “very satisfying” and 45.5 percent view it as “satisfying,” while 27.2 percent view it as “unsatisfying” and 12.2 percent as “very unsatisfying” in the past three years. The results showed that 50.7 percent of Taipei voters are very satisfied or satisfied with his remark that “the two sides of the Taiwan Strait are one family,” and 68.3 percent are very satisfied or satisfied with his decision not to remove all statues of Chiang Kai-shek （蔣介石） from the city. This indicates that most Taipei residents are relatively conservative in their political views and that they are inclined to stick with the “status quo,” the foundation said. The poll showed that 6.4 percent of voters identify with the DPP and 25.9 percent identify more closely with the DPP, compared with 5.3 percent who identify with the KMT and 23.6 percent who identify more closely with the KMT, while 4.8 percent abstained from answering the question. The results showed that Taipei residents’ party affiliation has shifted toward the pan-green camp （32.3 percent）, edging out the pan-blue camp （28.9 percent） by a narrow margin, You said. When asked about the poll results, Ko said that he thinks he is handling his mayoral duties well and that he is the “best advertisement for himself.” 新聞來源：TAIPEI TIMES 
You Ying-lung, second right, chairman of Taiwanese Public Opinion Foundation, yesterday releases the results of a poll during a news conference in Taipei, saying Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je’s approval rating is higher than that of all his possible opponents.
